    "Application to antibody therapeutics.",
    "The assessment of humanness is a critical step of antibody drug development, with the goal of ensuring that drug candidates have minimal risk for administration to patients.",
    "Therefore, we ran AbNatiV on therapeutic antibody sequences and averaged the humanness score of the heavy and light chains from the relevant AbNatiV model (that is, trained either on VH, Vκ or Vλ; Methods).",
    "More specifically, we evaluated the performance of the method on distinguishing 196 human therapeutics from 353 antibodies therapeutics of non-human origin (mouse, chimeric and humanized).",
